{
  "texts": [
    "Self-referential operational closure within indeterminacy is how a system can continue to exist.",
    "This represents a non-essentialist ontological perspective which contrasts with the European tradition of essentializing the existence of an entity as distinct from what is external to and with properties that are independent of its environment.",
    "In this view, the identity and properties of a system are not pre-given but emerge through ongoing processes of distinction, interaction, and adaptation.",
    "The system's boundaries and characteristics are, thus, fluid and contingent, shaped by continuous feedback loops with the environment.",
    "For example, the scientific system's understanding of authorship evolves as it interacts with technological innovations like generative AI, leading to new forms of collaboration and publication practices that redefine what it means to be an author."
  ]
}